The toll from floods in Bangladesh jumped Thursday to 54 people dead, with more than five million others displaced, after monsoon rains and Himalayan snowmelt caused rivers to overflow.
Flood relief workers in Bangladesh struggled Friday to reach millions of people stranded in their villages without food or clean water, officials said.
Monsoon floods ravaging Bangladesh for more than a week have killed about 46 people and displaced or marooned millions, authorities said Thursday.
At least 5 million people have either been marooned or displaced in the country's hardest-hit northern region.
